                    <span>Seventeen years ago I was a seriously depressed young mother facing a devastating divorce when I happened to come across this book in a  pharmacy.  When I first opened the book and began reading, I had the first glimmering of hope that I had had in a long time, and this book eventually changed my life, much for the better!  Although Dr. Peale's way of writing would seem somewhat old-fashioned to modern-minded people, his basic message is of hope, and if you follow his instructions, you CAN change your life!  Dr. Peale encourages people to "expect a miracle" and "act as if" a miracle can happen -- and it CAN!  This book is a classic, I'm so glad to see Amazon is selling it, and I cannot recommend it highly enough!   Why not try it yourself, and find out?  You can buy a used copy of the original here at Amazon for .01 cents!  You have nothing to lose -- and everything to gain.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Powerfully Inspiring!</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>3</span>
                      /
                      <span>3</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2003-11-26</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Dr. Peale begins by explaining the concept of imaging as a form of "mental engineering" which is derived from the term imagination. He goes on to add that "a long-held visualization of an objective or goal can become determinative." He says this process has worked for him. He cautions that this method is not some form of magic, that it opens doors, but once those doors open, it is up to the person to follow through with discipline, work, and persistence.<p>As a Christian, Dr. Peale points out that the power of imaging is secondary to a more important thought, that being that "there is an all-powerful Being in the universe who loves me and who is only a prayer away." He talks about a relationship with Jesus Christ being more significant than goal-accomplishment or any other thought, achievement, or creation seen or invisible.<p>This book will help you improve your quality of life because it contains so many truths. Through reading it you will gain a perspective that will help you to overcome the challenges you face. I recommend it highly.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">This book helped me to change my confusion into understandin</div>
